			<abstract>
				<p>Erich Nasch and Robert Weinberger provide a brief report of their activities for the Documentation campaign. In October 1945, they visited several former labor and concentration camps in Austria and Germany to gather evidence about the events of the Holocaust. In October–November
					1945, they travelled to Frankfurt am Main, where they got in touch with members of various organizations involved in war crime investigations, documentation of the Holocaust, committees for displaced persons, etc. In November–December 1945, they visited Paris and travelled to
					Brussels to meet some of the members of the World Jewish Congress.</p>
			</abstract>
